pr_title: Make it easy to record/update api-changes xml file with jbang script
pr_body:
Added a JBang script to make it easy to update the api-changes.xml file.

When you run revapi, it generates api-changes-suggestions.xml file in the target directory. This file contains suggestions of the new changes you might want to ignore. 

So when you run jbang script, it will take the suggestions and put it in api-changes.xml file. The api-changes.xml file contains the new changes you want to ignore.

To run revapi use this command in any of the modules:
`mvn -Papi-check -Drevapi.skip=false -DskipTests verify`

To run the JBang script:
`jbang revapi-update`

pr_title: Reduce false positives from revapi output/report
pr_body: Revapi report/output contains a lot of false positives(changes that shouldn't be relevant to revapi), this PR aims to reduce that.
